LAGOS â€“ The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Lagos Sector Command, has reiterated that motorists should always report any infractions of rickety or faulty vehicles to the appropriate authorities rather than just posting on social media. This is arising from a recent trending video of an articulated 40 feet containerized vehicle along Ikorodu Road, Lagos. Such incident according to the FRSC Lagos Sector Commander Olusegun Ogungbemide should be reported to FRSC via its Toll-free number 122 or sent to any of the FRSC social media handles Twitter or Instagram @FRSCnigeria or via Facebook. It should be noted that FRSC Lagos Command has 12 Unit Commands, 6 Outposts that can promptly impound such reported vehicles to avert causing calamities on the road. He further stated that road safety is a joint responsibility and crashes can be averted if promptly reported to the appropriate authorities.